 are brown, spherical berries, 8-10 mm in diameter.", "uses": "Benkara canthioides is a plant species that has been studied for its potential medicinal properties. Benkara canthioides is traditionally used in Indian medicine to treat various health conditions, including fever, rheumatism, and digestive issues. The plant's leaves and roots are used in Ayurvedic medicine to reduce inflammation and aid in wound healing. Further research is needed to fully understand the plant's medicinal uses and potential benefits. However, initial studies suggest that Benkara canthioides may have antimicrobial and antioxidant properties.", "taxonomy": "Benkara canthioides is a species of flowering plant in the family Rutaceae. It is native to tropical regions and belongs to the genus Benkara, which is a part of the citrus family. Benkara canthioides is a close relative of the genus Citrus and shares some similarities with citrus species. The plant is also known by its synonyms, including Limonia canthioides and Fortunella canthioides. Further research is needed to confirm the exact classification and relationships of Benkara canthioides within the Rutaceae family.", "benefits": "Benkara canthioides is a plant species known for its potential health benefits. It is said to have anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which may contribute to its ability to aid in wound healing and reduce the risk of infection. The plant's extracts may also possess antioxidant properties, helping to protect cells from damage and promote overall well-being. Additionally, Benkara canthioides has been traditionally used to treat various health conditions, including fever, cough, and respiratory issues. More research is needed to fully understand the plant's health benefits and potential applications.", "parts": "Benkara canthioides. The medicinal parts of Benkara canthioides have been traditionally used to treat various health issues. The plant's leaves, roots, and stems are known to possess medicinal properties. These parts are used to treat fever, digestive issues, and skin problems. The exact composition and efficacy of the medicinal parts are still being researched and documented.", "intro": "Benkara canthioides, also known as Wild Mahogany, is a tropical plant species in the family Rubiaceae, characterized by its unique, woody stems and clusters of small flowers. Traditionally, Benkara canthioides is valued for its potential health benefits, including anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant properties, which may contribute to its use in treating fever, cough, and respiratory issues. The bioactive constituents of Benkara canthioides include flavonoids, alkaloids, and phenolic compounds, including benzoic acid, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. In traditional medicine, Benkara canthioides is commonly prepared as a decoction, infusion, or tincture, often combined with other herbs, and is used to treat various ailments, including fever, rheumatism, and digestive issues."}